EventItemTitle: A Local Law in relation to the date of submission by the Mayor of the proposed executive budget and budget message, the date of submission by the Borough Presidents of recommendations in response to the Mayor’s executive budget, the date of publication of a report by the director of the independent budget office analyzing the executive budget, the date by which the Council hearings pertaining to the executive budget shall conclude, the date by which if the expense budget has not been adopted, the expense budget and tax rate adopted as modified for the current fiscal year shall be deemed to have been extended for the new fiscal year until such time as a new expense budget has been adopted, the date by which if a capital budget and a capital program have not been adopted, the unutilized portion of all prior capital appropriations shall be deemed reappropriated, the date of submission by the Mayor of an estimate of the probable amount of receipts, the date by which any person or organization may submit an official alternative estimate of revenues, the date by which if the Council has not fixed the tax rates for the ensuing fiscal year, the commissioner of finance shall be authorized to complete the assessment rolls using estimated rates, and related matters, relating to the fiscal year two thousand fifteen.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Parks and Recreation
EventItemTitle: A Local Law in relation to renaming two thoroughfares and public places in the Borough of the Bronx, East 177th Street, and to amend the official map of the city of New York accordingly.
EventItemMatterName: Name Change, Renaming two thoroughfares and public places, Bronx, East 177th Street.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Environmental Protection
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the New York city charter, the administrative code of the city of New York, the New York city building code, and the New York city mechanical code, in relation to the New York city air pollution control code.
EventItemMatterName: Air pollution control code.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Transportation
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to the New York city taxi and limousine commission’s critical drivers and persistent violators programs.
EventItemMatterName: NYC taxi and limousine commission’s critical drivers and persistent violators programs.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Education
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York City Department of Education to establish a comprehensive college preparation program, based on the college readiness model proposed by the Urban Youth Collaborative, to improve and expand college access for all students.
EventItemMatterName: Establish a comprehensive college preparation program.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Sanitation and Solid Waste Management
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to requiring that notices of violation issued by the department of sanitation be accompanied by a photograph of the alleged violation.
EventItemMatterName: Requiring that notices of violation issued by the department of sanitation be accompanied by a photograph of the alleged violation.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Transportation
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to bulk milk truck weight restrictions.
EventItemMatterName: Bulk milk truck weight restrictions.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Health
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to requiring photographic documentation of alleged violations identified during sanitary inspections of food service establishments.
EventItemMatterName: Requiring photographic documentation of alleged violations identified during sanitary inspections of food service establishments.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Transportation
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to a pilot program involving black box or telematics technology in taxis and street hail liveries.
EventItemMatterName: Pilot program involving black box or telematics technology in taxis and street hail liveries.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Transportation
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to the reporting of crash data involving taxi and limousine commission licensed vehicles.
EventItemMatterName: Reporting of crash data involving taxi and limousine commission licensed vehicles.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Transportation
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to requiring photographs to be included with certain notices of violation for parking violations.
EventItemMatterName: Requiring photographs to be included with certain notices of violation for parking violations.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Civil Service and Labor
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to a one year delay for businesses affected by Hurricane Sandy to comply with the Earned Sick Time Act.
EventItemMatterName: One year delay for businesses affected by Hurricane Sandy to comply with the Earned Sick Time Act.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Housing and Buildings
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to requiring the department of buildings to maintain a registry of restrictive covenants.
EventItemMatterName: Requiring the department of buildings to maintain a registry of restrictive covenants.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Small Business
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York State Legislature to pass and the Governor to sign S.6717 and A.8653, in relation to authorizing the creation of small business tax-deferred savings accounts.
EventItemMatterName: Authorizing the creation of small business tax-deferred savings accounts. (S.6717/A.8653)

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Veterans
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York State Legislature to pass, and the Governor to sign S.6865 and A.9135, legislation which would promote opportunities for service-disabled veteran owned small businesses in State contracting.
EventItemMatterName: Promote opportunities for service-disabled veteran owned small businesses in State contracting. (S.6865/A.9135)

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Governmental Operations
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the New York city charter, in relation to expanding the membership of the board of standards and appeals.
EventItemMatterName: Expanding the membership of the board of standards and appeals.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Governmental Operations
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the New York city charter, in relation to requiring the advice and consent of the city council for commissioners of the board of standards and appeals.
EventItemMatterName: Requiring the advice and consent of the city council for commissioners of the board of standards and appeals.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Governmental Operations
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the New York city charter, in relation to community involvement in decisions of the board of standards and appeals.
EventItemMatterName: Community involvement in decisions of the board of standards and appeals.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Public Housing
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York City Housing Authority to stop charging tenants a debit card convenience fee when a rent payment is made using a debit card.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Transportation
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the Metropolitan Transportation Authority (MTA) to establish a Metrocard discount fare program through which eligible non-profit organizations can receive and distribute discounted Metrocards to their clients.
EventItemMatterName: MTA to establish a Metrocard discount fare program through which eligible non-profit organizations can receive and distribute discounted Metrocards to their clients.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Transportation
EventItemTitle: Resolution strongly urging the Metropolitan Transportation Authority to provide greater advance notification for planned service disruptions.
EventItemMatterName: Strongly urging the MTA to provide greater advance notification for planned service disruptions.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Environmental Protection
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling on the New York State Legislature to increase the civil penalties to $2,500 for a first offense and $15,000 for each subsequent offense within a two year period for failure to comply with the utility notification requirements of Article 36 of the General Business Law.
EventItemMatterName: Increase the civil penalties to $2,500 for a first offense and $15,000 for each subsequent offense within a two year period for failure to comply with the utility notification requirements of Article 36 of the General Business Law.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Aging
EventItemTitle: Resolution urging the New York State Legislature to pass and the Governor to sign legislation that would enable the spouse of someone enrolled in the Senior Citizen Rent Increase Exemption Program (SCRIE) to continue receiving SCRIE benefits when the enrolled spouse dies, and the widow or widower is within 5 years of the age requirement for receipt of SCRIE
EventItemMatterName: Enable the spouse of someone enrolled in the Senior Citizen Rent Increase Exemption Program (SCRIE) to continue receiving SCRIE benefits when the enrolled spouse dies.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Public Safety
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to the creation of voluntary registry for persons with special medical needs.
EventItemMatterName: Creation of voluntary registry for persons with special medical needs.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Education
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to requiring the department of education to require parental consent prior to releasing personally identifiable student data.
EventItemMatterName: Requiring DOE to require parental consent prior to releasing personally identifiable student data.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Mental Health, Developmental Disability, Alcoholism, Drug Abuse and Disability Services
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to amending the silver alert program to include missing persons with developmental disabilities.
EventItemMatterName: Amending the silver alert program to include missing persons with developmental disabilities.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Mental Health, Developmental Disability, Alcoholism, Drug Abuse and Disability Services
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York State Office for People with Developmental Disabilities to include the use of GPS tracking devices as a covered service available under the People First Waiver.
EventItemMatterName: NYS Office for People with Developmental Disabilities to include the use of GPS tracking devices as a covered service available under the People First Waiver.
